The Mouse Who Woke Up For Christmas

by Luke A. Jones

You are in a Garden Shed.

You groggily awake from your hibernation to the deafening sound of your alarm clock. Better switch it off quick before it attracts attention.

You can see a Bed (containing Jessica), a Fireplace, a Wardrobe, a Toolbox, a Mantelpiece, an Alarm Clock, a Mirror, a Stocking, a Fridge and a Photo Frame.

You can go out.

> switch off clock

> switch off clock

You bring your paw down on top of the alarm clock and switch it off. The sudden silence is as deafening as the alarm itself.

Now you can think clearly you remember why you set the alarm. It was so that Jessica (your daughter) could see Christmas Day for the first time. She refused go into hibernation until you promised to wake her up. She's as stubborn as her mother, so you had to agree.

It's Christmas Eve morning, so plenty of time to gather the things you will need. Light a fire, find some food, find a stocking and hang it up,  find a present to give to Jessica and some beer for yourself.

You write a list on the back of a scrap of paper and put it in your pocket.
> x me

> x me

A distinguished gentleman mouse named Gerald. You have light tan fur, long whiskers and a pink tail.

You are wearing a pair of  Long Johns and a pair of pyjamas and slippers.
> i

> i
You are carrying a pair of  Long Johns (worn), a pair of pyjamas and slippers (worn) and a To Do List.
> x list

> x list
1. Light the fireplace.
2. Hang up Jessica's stocking on the mantelpiece.
3. Find a present for Jessica (and put it inside her stocking).
4. Buy some beer for yourself.
> x johns

> x johns

A pair of white woollen long johns.
> x pyjamas

> x pyjamas
Your sleeping attire consisting of a rather fetching red silk pyjama shirt, trousers, nightcap and a pair of slippers, with a fleur-de-lis pattern in black.

The label inside the pyjama's reads;

'Elite Couture'
handmade by P.Spider.
> x slippers

> x slippers

A pair of Persian slippers in gold and black leather. They curl up at the toes in an Aladdin style.
> x Jessica

> x Jessica

Your precious daughter Jessica. She lies soundly asleep, her snow-white and grey flecked fur rises and falls as she breathes. In her paw you can see that she is gripping a note, you gently prise it from her. It is a note addressed to Santa.
> x note

> x note
In Jessica's unsteady infant writing it reads:

A pang of hurt stabs at your chest, your wife Gemma went missing last summer, when it was so dry she left the garden to try and find water.

She never returned, and to add salt to the wound the weather broke that night in huge thunderstorm.

You held Jessica all night until she eventually cried herself to sleep.
> x bed

> x bed
A mouse sized four-poster bed with a crib attached at the bottom.
 In which there is Jessica.
> x crib

> x crib
A wooden crib attached to the foot of the bed, which Jessica sleeps in.
> x fireplace

> x fireplace

A fireplace fashioned out of an old tin can, with a carved wooden mantelpiece surround. There is a cylindrical metal chimney pipe which exits through a small hole in the shed wall.
> x mantelpiece

> x mantelpiece
A wooden mantelpiece surrounding the fire, a grapevine pattern is carved into it. The perfect place to hang up a stocking for Jessica (if you had a stocking and something to hang it up with).
> x pipe

> x pipe
A cylindrical metal pipe that acts as a chimney for the fireplace. It exits through a small hole in the shed wall.
> x hole

> x hole
A small hole in the wall of the shed, through which the chimney from the fireplace exits.
> x mirror

> x mirror

A full length (for a mouse) floor mirror with a wooden frame.

Looking into the mirror you see;

A distinguished gentleman mouse named Gerald. You have light tan fur, long whiskers and a pink tail.

You are wearing a pair of  Long Johns and a pair of pyjamas and slippers.
> x stocking

> x stocking

One of Jessica's knee-length socks, knitted by her mother.

It's ready to be hung up, but it looks like moths have been in the shed while you were asleep as it now has a large hole in the foot.
> x fridge

> x fridge

Your small white fridge, which is sadly devoid of beer.
> x frame

> x frame

A guilded photo frame with a polaroid photo of your family; your daughter Jessica, your wife Gemma and you.

