Brandishing your Rubber Boots you enter the Vegetable Patch.

You are in the Vegetable Patch.

The human who lives in the house is a keen gardener.

In the spring and summer there are wonderful beans and courgettes, followed by luscious cabbages and other assorted brassicas.

You try to not steal too many through the year, but you get the impression that the human doesn't mind too much anyway, he feeds the birds and even the squirrels.

Now in midwinter it is a bare and muddy patch of earth.

You can see a Spade, a Hole (containing a Coin), Stewart the Snail, a Large Stone and a Wheelbarrow.

