A magpie cache. Peter is obsessed with shiny things and guards them jealously.
It contains some Rings, a Metal Bar and Half of a metal watch strap.
> x rings

> x rings

A collection of various silver and gold rings.
> x bar

> x bar

A shiny silver metal bar.
> x strap

> x strap

A section of metal watch strap, judging by the distinctive linkage it was once part of a Tag Heur.
> talk to Peter

> talk to Peter

 "Hello Gerald, Have you seen any shiny things around the garden today?" says Peter.
> ask Peter about shiny

> ask Peter about shiny

"Oh do you like shiny things too?" says Peter, "I've been working on this collection for a couple of years now, the arrangement takes a lot of finessing."
> ask Peter about rings

> ask Peter about rings

"Nice aren't they!" says Peter

"A good selection of sizes and shapes, and so shiny!"
> ask Peter about strap

> ask Peter about strap

"I'm so pleased with it!" says Peter,

"I'd been looking for one for ages, but just couldn't find the time."
> put ball in collection

> put ball in collection

Peter hops over to the collection of shiny things,

"This isn't shiny!" says Peter and pushes the Cricket Ball over the side of the tree.

Below you hear a 'Bonk!' and a muffled yelp followed by a 'Thud!'
> take bar

> take bar

"Oi! That my shiny thing!" says Peter,

"I might let you have it if you can find something better to replace it with though. The feng shui isn't quite right with it."

Peter fusses and rearranges his shiny things.
