> in

> in

You step over the unconscious Weasel and enter the Squirrel Midden.

You are in The Nutcracker Night Club (Inside the Squirrel Midden).

It takes a few seconds for your eyes to adjust to the relative darkness...

You are in The Nutcracker Night Club (Inside the Squirrel Midden).

A somewhat seedy nightclub with a retro charm. The owner Cyril Squirrel is rumoured to be an ex boss of the notorious Nutcracker gang, named for their preferred method of punishment rather than their diet.

The room is decorated for Christmas with gaudy decorations hanging from the ceiling.

Some mid 1990's Ibiza trance track is booming out of the PA system.

You can see Cyril Squirrel, a Dance Floor, a Mirror Ball, a Bar, Lights, a bar mirror, Trevor Skunk, Ken Badger and Sam Hedgehog.

You can go out.

> x decorations

> x decorations

Silver bells, glitter baubals and all manner of brightly coloured tat.

Better not eat them else you'll get tinselitis.
> x Cyril

> x Cyril
Manning the bar is the owner of this establishment, one Cyril Squirrel.

Cyril is short for a squirrel but heavily built. He has a large gold chain around his thick neck.

He is wearing a sharp grey suit that matches his fur,and a black pin striped fedora hat with a white band.

He is currently polishing a pint glass and looking at you suspiciously.
> x floor

> x floor

It has ceased to be, passed on, it is pining for the fjords, run down the curtain and joined the choir invisible.
> x ball

> x ball
A spherical rotating ball covered in tiny mirror panels. It reflects light from the bottles suspended around it.
> x bottles

> x bottles
An array of bottles suspended from the ceiling, they are casting light on to the mirror ball which is then reflected around the room. On close inspection the bottles contain fireflies.

> take lights

> take lights

A mental image of the Weasel bouncer flashes in your mind and you decide that stealing from Cyril would be a bad idea, perhaps try asking him for one.
> x bar

> x bar
A long black marble bar. At the back of the bar is a room length mirror, reflecting the back of the bottles that are lined up against it.

A sign above the bar reads;

'Payment in nuts only!'
> x bar mirror

> x bar mirror

A large mirror that runs the whole length of the bar.

Looking into the mirror you see;

A distinguished gentleman mouse named Gerald. You have light tan fur, long whiskers and a pink tail.

You are wearing a pair of  Long Johns and Gardening Clothes.
> x Trevor

> x Trevor

Trevor is slumped against the bar, it looks like he's had a few too many already.

The air around him is heavy with whiskey fumes.
> x Ken

> x Ken

Ken Badger, fancies himself as pretty fly for a black and white guy.

He is dressed in ridiculously low slung jeans, over sized white t-shirt and an L.A. Lakers baseball cap (worn back to front).
> x Sam

> x Sam

An ex-raver and refugee of the '90's, his short attention span and infamous mood swings suggest that he left an important part of his brain behind in a club in Ibiza.

He is wearing black jeans and a white t-shirt with 'Manumission 1996' emblazoned on it.

He staring intently at the screen of an IPad.
> x ipad

> x ipad

An IPad that Sam is using to DJ, you can just make out that he has the Spotify App open.
> talk to Cyril

> talk to Cyril

"Alright Gerald me old china!" says Cyril,

"What can I do ya for?"

"By the way, you 'aven't seen Jack Rabbit anywhere 'ave you? 'E went missing after leaving the club the other night,"
> ask Cyril about Harry

> ask Cyril about Harry

"Yeah e's a er... business associate from a previous line of work I wuz in. " says Cyril.

"You wouldn't want to invite him to tea with your mother, but e's solid and reliable."
> ask Cyril about Jack

> ask Cyril about Jack

"'E was in 'ere the other night, was drunk as a skunk when he left..."

"Oi!" shouts Trevor Skunk, overhearing the conversation.

"Sorry Trevor! shouts Cyril.

Cyril rolls his eyes at you and continues,

"Anyway now I come to think of it was unusual for 'im, normally doesn't drink much. Anyway apparently 'e never got home."

"I 'ope nothing's 'appened to him, don't want any trouble around 'ere, bad for business!"
> ask Cyril about lights

> ask Cyril about lights

"Well," says Cyril, "If you want one of the light bottles you'll 'ave to do me a favour."

He nods his head in Sam's direction.

 "Sam's lost his edge, the dance floor is dead. Get that IPad off Sam and put on some tunes to get people dancing and I'll let you 'ave what you need."

Cyril shouts over to Sam,

"Oi Sam! Take a break and let Gerald take over."

Sam passes you the IPad.

> x ipad

> x ipad

An Ipad conected to the PA system via blutooth. Spotify app is currently open and playing an Ibiza 90's playlist.

Other playlist options on the home page are:

Goth and Industrial Metal (Enter 1 to choose)

1970's Rock (Enter 2 to choose)

Heavy Metal (Enter 3 to choose)

Cheesy Party Anthems  (Enter 4 to choose)

Hip-hop and Rap (Enter 5 to choose)

Enter choice...

> 4

You select the 'Cheesy Party Anthems' playlist,

Africa by Toto comes booming out of the PA and the dance floor fills up. You follow it up with Jump by Van Halen and now the dance floor is packed and more customers pour into the Nightclub.

Cyril wanders over to you, and hands you a light bottle,

 "Thanks Gerald, you're a natural, you must have done this is a previous life!"

" I think Sam has got the idea now so you can pass things back over to him."

Sam walks over to you, "Jez," he says, "No accounting for taste, but if that's what the punters want, it what they'll get". You hand him back the IPad.
> x light bottle

> x light bottle
A glass bottle containing fireflies, they emit a bright eerie green glow.
> x floor

> x floor

The dance floor is heaving, the cheesy playlist is doing the job.
> dance

> dance

You manage to find a free spot on the dance floor and dance along to Rosanna by Toto.
> talk to Ken

> talk to Ken

"Yo! What's up dog?" drawls Ken.
> ask Ken about Jack

> ask Ken about Jack

"Yeah bossman Cyril tells me he's gone AWOL," says Ken,

"Sounds like some trouble homie."
> talk to Trevor

> talk to Trevor

"Whazz happening matey?" slurs Trevor.
> ask Trevor about Jack

> ask Trevor about Jack

"Listen here" says Trevor and motions to you to come closer.

He breathes whiskey fumes all over you and wispers in your ear,

"Somethin funny goin on around here, you mark my wards, I mean words!"

Trevor battles to keep his eyes open as he sways to and fro.
> ask Cyril about stoat

> ask Cyril about stoat
"Yeah there was a stoat in 'ere the other night, I 'ad a go at 'arry for letting him in."

Cyril gestures towards the door.

"Rough as a badger's arse, and ...

"Oi" shouts Ken the Badger, overhearing the conversation

"Sorry Ken!" shouts Cyril.

"Anyway" says Cyril,

"'e kept pushing in at the bar. Said 'is name was Nick."
> ask Trevor about stoat

> ask Trevor about stoat

Breathing whiskey fumes all over you Trevor replies,

"Yeah I saw that git of a stoat on Tuesday, kept pushin in at the bar!"

 Trevor battles to stay upright as he sways to and fro.
> ask Ken about stoat

> ask Ken about stoat

"I wasn't in on Tuesday night but Cyril tells me there was some dodgy stoat hanging about." says Ken.

"Don't know why Harry let him, the fool!"
> ask Sam about stoat

> ask Sam about stoat

"Yeah man, there was some dodgy stoat in here Tuesday night, was causing hassle at the bar by pushing in and generally being ungroovy."
