> talk to Penelope

> talk to Penelope

Penelope glances up from her sewing whilst here hands continue to work at a mad pace.

"No time to chit-chat Gerald." says Penelope, " My daughter is getting married tomorrow and I'm having to alter her dress. She's had  too many mince flies!"

"Actually Gerald" she says, "Any chance you could do me a favour?"

"I still need to make Nancy a posy for her wedding day, some Holly and Mistletoe would be perfect if you can find some."

> ask Penelope about Gemma

> ask Penelope about Gemma

"Oh I'm sorry Gerald, I don't know where your wife could have got to, it's become a dangerous world out there, I never leave the garden these days."
> ask Penelope about Nancy

> ask Penelope about Nancy

"She drives me crazy, but I'll miss her when she moves away." says Penelope.

"Her fiance Itsy has place on the other side of town."
> give stocking to Penelope

> give stocking to Penelope

"Sorry Gerald, I don't have time to take on extra jobs at the moment," says Penelope.

"Perhaps if you can help me out by finding me some holly and mistletoe for a wedding posy, I'll be able to find the time to help you."
> give holly to Penelope

> give holly to Penelope

You hand the mistletoe and holly to Penelope Spider.

"Oh thank you so much Gerald", says Penelope.

"That has saved me so much time and trouble, if I can do any favour for you please let me know."
> give stocking to Penelope

> give stocking to Penelope

Penelope takes the stocking from you an examines it.

"Hmm, shouldn't be too much bother" she says.

With lightening speed holding the stocking with one leg, she grabs a reel of cotton with another and threads a needle being held by another leg.

In a blur she darns the sock, ties off the end of the thread, and bites of the excess with her fangs.

"There you go", she says,

"I hope Jessica wakes up to something nice inside it, she deserves a happy day the poor mite."

She hands you the mended stocking.
