> x Santa

> x Santa

A portly, smiling, white-bearded man with half-moon spectacles, and a twinkle in his eye.

He's wearing a red coat with white collar and cuffs, white-cuffed red trousers, and black leather belt and boots.

He's sat on a large leather armchair.
> x elf

> x elf

You can see why this guy is the 'Chief' Elf, he's taller than Santa!

His lanky frame is all arms and legs, he's wearing a green robe trimmed with white fur, a green and yellow striped cone-shaped hat, and yellow stockings.
> x elves

> x elves

The elves are a blur of activity, you've never seen people work so fast before.
> talk to Santa

> talk to Santa

"Hello Gerald" says Santa,

"A Merry Christmas to you!" "We've had a few problems this year, but we seem to be back on track."
> give note to Santa

> give note to Santa

You climb up Santa's leg and sit on his knee. Santa strokes your head and says,

 "Well then Gerald, you've been a good lad, what can I do for you?"

You hand Santa the letter from Jessica.

"Well, well what this then?" says Santa,

He reads the note and a shadow crosses his face. He wipes a tear from the corner of his eye, clears his throat and says,

"I'm sorry Gerald, it must be tough for you keeping a brave face on things for Jessica, and your wife Gemma is a good lass."

"I have some magic about me, my omniscience isn't as powerful as children think, but my intuition tells me that she is still alive, but lost somewhere."

"I'll tell you what, I'll send the word out to my helpers around the country and see if they have seen or heard anything."

He rummages in his sack and pulls out a wrapped present,

 "Here, save me calling round to night, put this is Jessica's stocking".

He hands you the present and you take it.

"Oh and one for you too Gerald, Merry Christmas!"

He hands you a second parcel.
> x Jessica's present

> x Jessica's present

A small wrapped present that Santa gave you for Jessica.

The wrapping paper is pink with a pattern of rainbows and unicorns. It is tied with a yellow bow.
> open your present

> open your present
You open it.

You excitedly rip open your present from Santa, for a few seconds you lose yourself in the moment and feel like a child again.

It's a Ninja Outfit!

"Ho Ho Ho!" says Santa,

"I think it will make a nice addition to your wardrobe Gerald. Merry Christmas!"
> x ninja

> x ninja

The whole suit is made from black silk and is a dark as misery's woeful night.

There are loose trousers with cloth wrappings at the calf and ankles, a shirt with wrappings at the wrists, a hood and a mask.

There is also a pair of split toe suede boots.

Attached to a belt worn around the waist is a rather vicious looking grappling hook on a length of black rope.

Although a present from Santa, it doesn't look like this was made by elves.

> remove clothes

> remove clothes
You take it off.
> wear ninja

> wear ninja
You put it on.
> out

> out

You are in the Town Square.

The town square is dark and eerily quiet, all the shops look closed.

To the north lies Santa's Workshop where there is a light on, to the south there is a Cheese Shop (The Cheese Hamlet), to the east lies the Cross Key's Inn and to the Northeast is Tib Street.

You can go west, north, northeast, east or south.

> ne

> ne

You are in a Tib Street.

A quiet back street of town, to the East lies the 'Petcetera' pet shop.

You can go southwest or east.

> e

> e

You are an Outside Petcetera Pet Store.

It is dark and cold this end of the street, the snow is starting to fall heavier now.

The  store is closed and dark, but you can see a light on in the 1st floor (2nd floor for you American players) window.

You can see a Shop Door and a Petecetera Pet Store.

You can go in or west.

> x store

> x store

The pet store is painted blue and yellow, with a large sign across the front with the shop's name in large illuminated red letters (turned off at the moment).

The glass doors are shut but a banner in the window reads.

'Grand Opening, Boxing Day, 10am!'

The inside of the store is too dark to make out, except for what looks like illuminated tropical fish tanks somewhere at the back of the store.

On the first floor you can see a light on in one of the windows.

The store gives you the creeps, being held captive as a human's pet is one of your biggest fears.
> in

> in
The store is closed and the door is locked.
> throw hook

> throw hook

You take the grappling hook, after spinning it a few times above your head to open the hooks you throw it towards to upper storey window ledge.

It sails into the air pulling the rope attached to your waist.

You hear a 'clank' as it lands against the window's decorative lintel.

You give it a tug and it feels like it had gripped tight on to something.

You climb the rope up to the upper storey window ledge.

You are Outside Upper Storey Window.

You are outside the upper storey window of the pet store, there is a light on inside the room, and you can hear raised voices.

You can see a Window.

You can go in or down.

> listen

> listen

Listening carefully at the window you can hear an argument;

"I want a bigger cut Nick, I'm taking a hell of a risk with my job at the Nutcracker!'

"Shut it Harry! You're getting paid well enough for the risk, any more of your cheek and we'll sell you on Boxing Day!"

"Fine, I don't want any more to do with this madness, I'm off'

You hear a door slam.

> x window

> x window

Being careful to remain hidden you can see Nick Stoat pacing up and down the office, puffing on a cigar.

After a while he collapses into the office chair with a sigh, stubs out his cigar, and begins to nod off.

Looks like now's your chance if you want to get in there.
> open window

> open window

You carefully open the window just wide enough that you can squeeze through.
> in

> in

You climb through the window and carefully drop to the floor and sneak across the room, but just as you pass Nick one of the floorboards creaks.

In a shot Nick Stoat is up and on you,

"Ah more stock for the shop!" says Nick with a wicked grin.

He takes all your equipment and makes you strip down to your Long Johns.

He throws all your clothes and possessions into the office waste paper bin.

"Got just the place for you!" snarls Nick.

He opens up one of the cages and throws you in it.

"See you on Boxing Day, Merry Christmas! Haw haw haw!"

Nick slams the door of the cage shut, turns off the light in the office and leaves.

Press any key to continue.

You are Inside A Cage (In the Pet Store Office).

A filthy wire pet cage, there is damp straw on the floor, and there is an empty water bottle and food bowl.

The light is off in the office, but there is bright moonlight streaming through the window so you can see out of the cage and into the pet store office where you can see:

Banners and balloons ready for the opening day, various boxes and a chair and desk (with paperwork stacked on it).

On the wall is a map.

On either side of your cage you can see two others.

You can see Small Cage, a Large Cage, a Food Bowl, Water Bottle, a Moonbeam, a Window and a Waste Paper Bin.

You can go out.

You are Inside A Cage (In the Pet Store Office).

A filthy wire pet cage, there is damp straw on the floor, and there is an empty water bottle and food bowl.

The light is off in the office, but there is bright moonlight streaming through the window so you can see out of the cage and into the pet store office where you can see:

Banners and balloons ready for the opening day, various boxes and a chair and desk (with paperwork stacked on it).

On the wall is a map.

On either side of your cage you can see two others.

You can see Small Cage, a Large Cage, a Food Bowl, Water Bottle, a Moonbeam, a Window and a Waste Paper Bin.

You can go out.

> x banners

> x banners

Banners that read 'Welcome to our Opening Day!' and '50% off all pets!'
> x balloons

> x balloons

Blue and yellow balloons (same colour scheme as the outside of the shop).
> x boxes

> x boxes

Carboard boxes with more banners and leaflets bursting out.
> x chair

> x chair

A generic swivel office chair, black with scuffed plastic arms.
> x desk

> x desk

A wooden and tatty office desk.
> x straw

> x straw
Filthy damp straw.
> x map

> x map

What looks like a map of the town with different locations circled in red, with lines drawn to photos, you recognise one of the photos of the outside of the Nutcracker nightclub.

> x small cage

> x small cage

A small wire cage, almost identical to the one that you are trapped in.

It contains Gemma.
> x Gemma

> x Gemma

It's your beautiful wife Gemma!

She has chestnut and dark chocolate coloured fur, and bright green eyes.

Gemma is dressed in the clothes she left home in months ago, now reduced to rags.

She is looking thin, but there is a determined and stoical look in her face.
> x rags

> x rags

Gemma's pretty yellow dress with the red flowers on is reduced to little more than rags.
> x large cage

> x large cage

A large filthy wire cage.
It contains Jack Rabbit.
> x Jack

> x Jack

Poor old Jack Rabbit, his snow white fur is grey with grime, and there is a vivid red patch on his chest where his fur has been ripped.

He is wearing his usual blue denim dungarees.
> x bowl

> x bowl
A round, thin and flat silver coloured metal bowl, it is dirty and dull.
> x bottle

> x bottle

An inverted water bottle tied to the cage you are in, it is dirty and empty.
> x moonbeam

> x moonbeam
A bright ray of moonlight, that lands on the floor of Jack's cage.
> x window

> x window

The window where you came in is stil open a jar. Bright moonlight is streaming in, hitting Jack's cage.
> x bin

> x bin
The waste paper bin where Nick threw all your clothes and possessions.
> talk to Gemma

> talk to Gemma

"Oh Gerald! I thought I'd never see you again!" says Gemma.

"The Stoat has had me locked up here for weeks, we were at another pet store out of town,"

"Nick ran up a load of bills and then did a midnight flit. He's opened this place with the help of some evil human called Ebeneezer."

"I kept biting the humans that tried to buy me, so Nick locked me up here instead."

"Anyway, how's Jessica?!"

"She's fine!" you reply, "but she has been miserable without you, we both have. She's hibernating at the moment but I promised I'd wake her up to see Christmas Day."

"I hope you've been looking after yourself Gerald, those long johns are filthy!" says Gemma.

> talk to Jack

> talk to Jack

"Hullo Gerald!" says Jack, "It's good to see you, but sorry you've been trapped too."

"I heard you got kidnapped after leaving the Nutcracker" you say.

"Yes" says Jack," two guys jumped me on my way home,"

"I tried to fight them off, but they must have spiked my drinks too, they knocked me out, next thing I know I'm here."
> take bowl

> take bowl
You pick it up.
> polish bowl

> polish bowl

You attempt to polish to bowl on your long johns, but they are grimy and greasy and you feel embarrassed.

"Here" shouts Gemma, "try this!"

She rips off a strip from the bottom of her raggedy dress and passes it to you through the bars of her cage, you reach out to grab it, and softly stroke the back of her paw as you take it.

Your eyes meet, and for a second you are frozen in the moment and love swells your heart.

"Thanks baby" you say, "I've missed you so much,"
> polish bowl

> polish bowl

Using the strip of rag from Gemma's dress you clean and polish the food bowl till it is so shiny you can see your face in it.
> give bowl to Jack

> give bowl to Jack

You pass the food bowl to Jack through the bars of your cage., it just about fits sideways through.

Jack grabs it and pulls it inside his cage, as he does so the bowl catches the moonbeam and reflects a super bright beam of light back out of the window.

A few seconds later there is a squawk and a flap of wings at the window, and Peter Magpie appears,

"Shiny Shiny Moon-Shiny Shiny!" exclaims Peter, hopping excitedly from foot to foot.

He jumps down to the floor and goes over to Jack's Cage and examines the shiny food bowl.

"Oooh" sighs Peter, "It's all sheeny, so lustrous, all agleam..."

Peter's eyes roll back in his head.

"Alright Peter, that's enough!" you say, Peter snaps out of it and hops over to your cage.

> talk to peter

> talk to peter

"Hello Gerald!" says Peter, "What are you doing in that cage? It doesn't look very shiny to me."

You patiently explain to Peter what's been going on, but his attention keeps getting drawn to the food bowl reflecting the moonlight in Jack cage.

Eventually you say to Peter, "Look Peter, you can have the moon shiny thing if you can open this cage for me?"

Peter cocks his head and looks at the cage door, "Well its a bit grubby, but OK", he fiddles with the catch, you push against the door and it opens.

Now to release Jack and Gemma.

> out

> out

You are in a Pet Store Office.

What looks like an office and general storage area for the Pet Store.

There are banners and balloons ready for the opening day, various boxes and a chair and desk (with paperwork stacked on it).

On the wall is a map, and below that what looks like a couple of cages.

You can see a paperwork, a desk, a cages, Your Cage, a Window, a Chair, a Gemma's Cage (containing Gemma), Jack's Cage (containing Jack Rabbit), Office Door and a Waste Paper Bin.

You can go in or out.

> open Gemma's cage

> open Gemma's cage
You open it.

You unlock and open the cage door. Gemma runs out and embraces you, you hug her till you arms ache.

"Take me home Gerald," says Gemma.
> open Jack's cage

> open Jack's cage
You open it.

You unlock and open the door to Jack's cage. Jack stumbles out, unsteady on his feet.

"Thanks Gerald, don't think I would have lasted much longer in there, Nick thinks it's fun to deprive us of food and water."

Jack hands the shiny food bowl to Peter.

"Ooooh Moon Shiny thing! Shiny like the moon, shiny shiny!"

Peter flies out of the window and into the night. The night sky has a pale blue hue, dawn is approaching.

> x bin

> x bin

A metal waste paper bin, where Nick threw all your clothes and possesions.
It contains Jessica's present from Santa, Gardening Clothes and a Ninja Outfit (including grappling hook).
> take clothes

> take clothes
You pick it up.
> take present

> take present
> take ninja

> take ninja
You pick it up.
> wear ninja

> wear ninja
You put it on.
> out

> out

"Come on let's get out of here!" you exclaim and head for the window (wondering how the hell you are going to get Gemma and Jack back down to the ground).

As you approach the window it slides open, and the face of the Chief Elf appears,

"Hey, where did that devil Nick get to?!"

All three of you point towards the office door.

"Right," says the Chief, "We'll deal with him and help out the rest of the animals he's locked up in the shop."

The Chief clambers his huge frame into the office, puts his fingers in his mouth and gives a loud whistle, a gang of elves armed with baseball bats climb in through the window.

"Let's give the guy at the top of the naughty list what he deserves for Christmas lads!" says the Chief Elf, he opens the office door and heads out with the elves behind him.

Press any key to continue

The three of you climb out of the window on to the window ledge, there floating in the air is Santa on his Sleigh with his reindeer at the front, he pats the seat next to him and says,

"Well come on then, I'll give you a lift, it will be light soon! Ho Ho Ho!"

You climb in and in a matter of seconds you are back at the garden.

You and Gemma climb out of the sleigh, "Thanks Santa!", "No problem, give my love to Jessica, I'll take Jack home.

Jack waves and says "Merry Christmas!"

Santa takes off into the sky, you take Gemma's hand and enter the shed together, you're home at last.

 press any key to continue

You are in a Garden Shed.

A rickety garden shed that has been your home for the last couple of years.

You can see a Bed (containing Jessica), a Fireplace (containing a Flaming Charcoal), a Wardrobe (containing a Smart Suit and a pair of pyjamas and slippers), a Toolbox, a Mantelpiece (on which there is a Jessica's Stocking (fixed) and a Nail), an Alarm Clock, a Mirror, a Fridge, a Photo Frame, a To Do List, a Flyer, a Machete, a Light Bottle, an Oily Rag, A Roll of Duct Tape, a Scrap of Fur, a Washing up sponge, a Pair of Sharp Nail Scissors, a Newspaper page, an Empty Bucket, a Crowbar and Gemma.

You can go out.

> put present in stocking

> put present in stocking

You excitedly put the present inside Jessica's stocking, you can't wait to see her little face light up when she opens it.
> x list

> x list
1. Light the fireplace.
2. Hang up Jessica's stocking on the mantelpiece.
3. Find a present for Jessica (and put it inside her stocking).
4. Buy some beer for yourself.
> wake Jessica

> wake Jessica

You gently shake Jessica. After a few moments she slowly opens her eyes and looks at you.

"Merry Christmas sweetheart!" you say.

"Look what Santa brought you!" you pull Gemma close to you.

"Mummy!" exclaims Jessica, she jumps into her mother's arms and bursts into tears, you hug them both.

You spend a wonderful Christmas Day together, The fire is warm and cosy, in the afternoon Jon Pigeon calls round and plays games with Jessica, her present from Santa was a packet of playing cards. Jon shows her how to cheat when dealing.

In the evening Gemma sings Christmas songs with Jessica sat on her lap, and you enjoy your Christmas Ale.

As the evening wears on Jessica's eyes grow heavy, until she falls asleep. You tuck her into her crib.

You put out the fire, set the alarm for spring and climb into bed with Gemma, you cuddle each other all up and all is right with the world.

The End

(press any key for credits)

